# {{project_name}}

Scaffolded with `comet new`. A Rocket-on-Cloudflare-Workers app backed by
Nebula and D1.

## Set up the database

Migrations are generated from the `#[derive(Entity)]` structs under `src/`,
not hand-written. Generate the first one (and the schema snapshot future
`comet migrate` calls diff against):

```sh
comet migrate init
```

Then apply it locally:

```sh
npx wrangler d1 migrations apply {{db_binding}} --local
```

## Develop

```sh
npm install
npm run dev
```

## Deploy

```sh
npm run deploy
```

## Changing the schema

Add entities with `comet generate entity <Name>`, then run
`comet migrate generate <name>` to turn schema changes into a new migration
file. `comet migrate status` shows pending changes without writing anything.
